snippet.textDisplay:
Im a small kid.

165 cm and 45 kg.

I’ve been eating a bowl of cereal and milk or two slices of bread every morning.

Then for afternoon i’d get a piece of fried chicken (chicken breast) and a plate of white rice and mineral water for drinks. The same goes for dinner.

My workout routine is doing push-ups, pull ups, wall sit and lunges. ( adds +3 push-ups per day, +1 pull up per day, +3 seconds wall sit per day and +3 lunges per day )

Currently at 80 push ups , 30 pull ups, 1 minute 30 seconds wall sit and 80 lunges.

I do not have weights nor can go to the gym due to personal reasons.

snippet.textDisplay:
I do 30 mins of 6mph
Then I do shoulder press for 10 minutes I do seated weighted row for 10 minutes then I do chest fly for 10 minutes, I do tricep pull down for 15 minutes I do bicep curls for 15 minutes ( all drop sets to get the max fatigue possible) then I do half an hour on the bikes I put the seat low so I targets my stomach more and I do it at a low 5 resistance, then I finish of half an hour of sit ups with a 10kg menicne ball , I do this 5 times a week with two rest days

Btw do a weight that’s difficult but not too high so you Injur yourself do 10 reps and stop and take as long as you need I usually take 10-15 seconds then do 10 again

But vick you are an inspiration for showing you’ve started , any person going to the gym or trying to better yourself is an inspiration , do you and be happy lmao
